annote={Recent research on relay node placement in Wireless Sensor Networks mostly focuses on connectivity establishment. Connectivity is one of the most crucial issue, since most of the actions are taken collaboratively. In addition, sensors are small battery operated devices. Usually after the deployment of wireless sensor networks, it is impossible to access a sensor node and change the battery. Once the battery is depleted the node dies. The most important source of energy consumption in sensor networks is message transmission. The energy required to transmit data is directly proportional to $r^4$ where $r$ is the distance between source and destination.},
